description:
Exclusive Design- Easy Care
All fabrics have been exclusively designed for Harry Rosen- Signature Label Patterns developed with customized  weaves and special textures  that reflect  the latest color stories for the season.
Fabric have been finished with Easy Care Finish for added  convenience and quick wrinkle recovery from ironing which is Oeko- Tex certified
Oeko-Tex labels and certificates confirm the human-ecological safety of textile products and articles from all stages of production (raw materials and fibres, yarns, fabrics, ready-to-use end products) along the textile value chain and also attest to socially and environmentally sound conditions in production facilities. 
About Compact Yarns 
All fabrics used to make up Harry Rosen- Signature shirts has been made with Compact yarns, This type of yarn is a higher quality yarn that is smoother and finer than non-compacted yarns.  Fabrics woven from these yarns often feel finer and smoother than you would expect based on their thread count alone.  For example. a 100s 2ply-Yarn compact fabric will feel like a 160s two-ply made from non compacted yarns. 
Supima Cotton 
Not all cottons are equal. Supima and regular cotton are in fact two different and distinct species of cotton. The most common type of cotton grown around the world typically have a fiber length of only about 1 inch, whereas Supima cotton’s fiber averages 1.5 inches. Shorter fibers produce yarns that are rougher and subject to pilling on the surface of the product, while longer fibers contribute to the strength and softness of apparel , ensuring that they are more comfortable, retain color longer. 
2 Ply Fabrics 
Shirting made up in 2 ply fabrics construction is regarded as being of primary importance to finished garments as the dimensional stability achieved using 2ply yarns is much more superior to Garments made from fabrics without dimensional stability( single ply yarns)  that  may change shape after laundering, which is undesirable for the wearers. 
Shirt Construction
All Harry Rosen- Signature shirts are made in Canada as it emphasizes fine craftmanship and attention to detail. All trimming and findings are sourced from Europe
